{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584161"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:40:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:40:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14413"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14413","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14413"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.93,0.04,0.02,0.02,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7108"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55251"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7108","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7108"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14413"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"40775"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4903"},{"type":"tags","id":"4905"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"6640"},{"type":"tags","id":"8426"},{"type":"tags","id":"9858"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16964"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17149"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55251","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55251"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cardiac cycle consists of a series of coordinated events that occur in the heart during each heartbeat. These events are precisely timed to ensure efficient blood flow through the heart and into the circulation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following components of the cardiac cycle occurs during ventricular systole?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Isovolumetric ventricular contraction","Rapid ventricular filling","Isovolumetric ventricular relaxation","Atrial systole","Slow ventricular filling"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eisovolumetric ventricular contraction\u003C/strong\u003E, which occurs during ventricular systole. This phase begins immediately after the closure of the atrioventricular valves (mitral and tricuspid) and marks the start of ventricular systole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERapid ventricular filling\u003C/strong\u003E occurs during early diastole when the ventricles relax and the atrioventricular valves open, allowing blood to flow rapidly from the atria into the ventricles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIsovolumetric ventricular relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E takes place at the beginning of ventricular diastole, after the closure of the semilunar valves (aortic and pulmonary) and before the opening of the atrioventricular valves.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAtrial systole\u003C/strong\u003E occurs at the end of ventricular diastole, just before the onset of ventricular systole. It contributes to the final filling of the ventricles before contraction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESlow ventricular filling\u003C/strong\u003E, also known as diastasis, is a period of reduced filling that occurs during mid-diastole, between the rapid filling phase and atrial systole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the timing of these events in the cardiac cycle is essential for interpreting heart sounds, electrocardiograms, and pressure changes within the heart chambers.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Isovolumetric ventricular contraction occurs during the early phase of ventricular systole in the cardiac cycle.","The cardiac cycle consists of systole (contraction) and diastole (relaxation) phases for both atria and ventricles.","Understanding the timing of cardiac events is crucial for interpreting heart sounds and pressure changes in the heart chambers."],"references":["Tortora, G. J., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Cooke, J., Di Pietro, F., Diversi, T., ... \u0026 Summers, S.. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 3rd Asia-Pacific Edition. 2022. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Fukuta H, Little WC. The cardiac cycle and the physiologic basis of left ventricular contraction, ejection, relaxation, and filling. Heart Fail Clin. 2008 Jan;4(1):1-11. doi: 10.1016/j.hfc.2007.10.004. PMID: 18313620; PMCID: PMC2390899."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"40775"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14413"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"40775","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/40775"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-14T13:16:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-14T13:16:38+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7108"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55251"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","na